1
00:01:28,940 --> 00:01:35,580
Winter Begonia

2
00:01:35,580 --> 00:01:38,060
Episode 8

3
00:01:39,860 --> 00:01:40,580
I’m coming. Coming.

4
00:01:40,740 --> 00:01:41,420
Quick. Quick. Quick.

5
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:42,580
Why did it take you so long?

6
00:01:45,140 --> 00:01:45,860
Leader.

7
00:01:46,180 --> 00:01:47,580
Are you hungry, leader?

8
00:01:47,620 --> 00:01:49,020
I bought pork shoulder.

9
00:01:49,140 --> 00:01:50,900
Come out and eat something first,

10
00:01:50,900 --> 00:01:52,060
okay, leader?

11
00:01:55,460 --> 00:01:56,979
Pork shoulder, leader.

12
00:01:59,580 --> 00:02:00,580
He didn’t reply.

13
00:02:02,740 --> 00:02:03,580
Oh, no.

14
00:02:04,340 --> 00:02:05,940
- Leader. - He’s not eating anything.

15
00:02:06,900 --> 00:02:08,580
Looks like he’s really angry.

16
00:02:10,180 --> 00:02:12,180
Those vicious traitors.

17
00:02:13,180 --> 00:02:14,900
We count on him to make a decision.

18
00:02:15,060 --> 00:02:16,780
He can’t throw up his job now.

19
00:02:17,340 --> 00:02:19,060
He has to tell us

20
00:02:19,620 --> 00:02:21,340
what we should do.

21
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:22,540
Leader,

22
00:02:23,780 --> 00:02:24,860
couldan you cut it out now?

23
00:02:30,700 --> 00:02:32,660
When you fell out with Jiang Mengping,

24
00:02:34,220 --> 00:02:35,340
we obeyed you.

25
00:02:37,420 --> 00:02:39,060
You wanted to go back to BeipingPeking

26
00:02:40,420 --> 00:02:41,980
and we also obeyed you.

27
00:02:42,579 --> 00:02:44,220
I even abandoned my fiancee.

28
00:02:44,340 --> 00:02:45,660
I’ve done all I can.

29
00:02:48,740 --> 00:02:49,780
You wanted to change our plays.

30
00:02:50,300 --> 00:02:50,900
Okay.

31
00:02:51,460 --> 00:02:52,220
You’re the lead.

32
00:02:52,380 --> 00:02:54,020
You can change them as you please.

33
00:02:54,420 --> 00:02:55,300
You were just heckled

34
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:56,460
by the audience.

35
00:02:56,900 --> 00:02:58,260
We should obey you.

36
00:02:59,180 --> 00:03:00,900
But after we listened to you

37
00:03:00,900 --> 00:03:01,700
and listened to you,

38
00:03:01,700 --> 00:03:03,500
we’re going to starve now.

39
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:05,180
You think you can hideing there?

40
00:03:05,220 --> 00:03:06,580
No way!

41
00:03:06,980 --> 00:03:08,420
Shang Xirui, get out.

42
00:03:08,420 --> 00:03:09,540
What are you doing, Shijiu?

43
00:03:09,540 --> 00:03:10,660
Stop it.

44
00:03:10,660 --> 00:03:11,340
Get out!

45
00:03:11,340 --> 00:03:12,700
- Let go of me. - Stop.

46
00:03:16,980 --> 00:03:17,900
Shang Xirui,

47
00:03:21,860 --> 00:03:23,300
when our old leader was alive,

48
00:03:24,860 --> 00:03:27,100
Empress Dowager Cixi invited him to sing in the palace.

49
00:03:28,980 --> 00:03:30,020
He was as famous

50
00:03:31,100 --> 00:03:33,740
as Ning Jiulang and Hou Yukui.

51
00:03:34,940 --> 00:03:35,940
How promising we were.

52
00:03:37,060 --> 00:03:38,620
Now you’re in charge of Shuiyun Theater.

53
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:40,980
If you can’t develop it,

54
00:03:41,620 --> 00:03:43,900
at least you should maintain it.

55
00:03:46,220 --> 00:03:47,380
But what you dodid

56
00:03:48,540 --> 00:03:51,579
is just losing your temper,

57
00:03:51,700 --> 00:03:53,060
doing whatever you want

58
00:03:53,220 --> 00:03:55,140
and taking us to a blind alley every day.

59
00:03:58,860 --> 00:04:00,100
Listen, Shang Xirui.

60
00:04:01,460 --> 00:04:03,340
This troupe is called Shuiyun Theater

61
00:04:03,380 --> 00:04:04,780
but not the Shang Troupe.

62
00:04:05,180 --> 00:04:06,660
I’m fed up with you!

63
00:04:06,660 --> 00:04:07,740
- Alright, calm down. - Let go!

64
00:04:07,740 --> 00:04:08,580
Shijiu.

65
00:04:08,580 --> 00:04:09,380
Shijiu. Shijiu.

66
00:04:09,380 --> 00:04:10,340
Shijiu!

67
00:04:12,940 --> 00:04:15,340
Leader, come out. Leader.

68
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:16,540
Come out.

69
00:04:20,420 --> 00:04:21,140
I just don’t believe it.

70
00:04:21,380 --> 00:04:22,700
I can live without you.

71
00:04:29,060 --> 00:04:29,740
What?

72
00:04:29,940 --> 00:04:31,460
You finally got out of your shell?.

73
00:04:33,260 --> 00:04:34,460
Shijiu,

74
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:36,300
if you leave,

75
00:04:36,780 --> 00:04:38,780
I’ll lose a helper.

76
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:39,980
You only have one helper

77
00:04:40,020 --> 00:04:41,140
and she got married.

78
00:04:41,180 --> 00:04:42,460
What kind of helper am I?

79
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:54,340
Mr. Cheng,

80
00:04:54,620 --> 00:04:56,100
I came to China

81
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:59,700
to explain something

82
00:05:00,260 --> 00:05:01,220
and apologize to you.

83
00:05:01,980 --> 00:05:04,780
I’m not able to strengthen Cave Liuxian.

84
00:05:05,740 --> 00:05:09,260
Actually corrosion and falling stones there

85
00:05:09,260 --> 00:05:11,340
aren’t the problems.

86
00:05:11,380 --> 00:05:12,740
The hardest part is the bearing of weight.

87
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:16,780
The whole mountain is on that cave.

88
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:18,420
I calculated the bearing value.

89
00:05:19,380 --> 00:05:22,540
Common steel materials can’t bear that weight at all.

90
00:05:22,940 --> 00:05:24,100
In today’s world,

91
00:05:24,260 --> 00:05:26,820
only some special alloys that we Germans use

92
00:05:26,820 --> 00:05:29,580
to make components of planes

93
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:31,860
can be that strong.

94
00:05:33,460 --> 00:05:34,460
I’ll can buy them

95
00:05:35,060 --> 00:05:36,300
no matter how much they costare.

96
00:05:38,020 --> 00:05:40,860
It’s true that you’re a rich man.

97
00:05:41,659 --> 00:05:47,100
But those materials are under control of the army

98
00:05:47,860 --> 00:05:49,900
and can’t be sold or bought at the market.

99
00:05:50,340 --> 00:05:53,740
Even if you can buy enough materials,

100
00:05:54,140 --> 00:05:58,700
you still need German engineers to put it up,

101
00:05:59,100 --> 00:06:01,660
which is out of the question in China.

102
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:04,620
You mean there’s no way we can do it?

103
00:06:05,660 --> 00:06:06,380
No.Yes.

104
00:06:07,220 --> 00:06:09,780
At least it’s out of my reach.

105
00:06:10,780 --> 00:06:11,780
I’m sorry.

106
00:06:14,180 --> 00:06:18,900
I’ve deducted the traveling and design cost.

107
00:06:19,380 --> 00:06:21,580
The rest of the deposit will be returned now.

108
00:06:23,180 --> 00:06:23,860
Give it to me.

109
00:06:29,140 --> 00:06:29,940
Okay,

110
00:06:30,220 --> 00:06:32,820
I’ll see you around, then.

111
00:06:34,700 --> 00:06:36,860
If there’s not something urgent you need to do,

112
00:06:37,380 --> 00:06:39,540
please have lunch here.

113
00:06:40,060 --> 00:06:41,340
You have come

114
00:06:41,460 --> 00:06:42,420
a long way.

115
00:06:42,740 --> 00:06:44,380
I’m really grateful to you.

116
00:06:46,140 --> 00:06:47,100
- Well... - Yes, Mr. Xin.

117
00:06:47,620 --> 00:06:48,980
We haven’t seen each other for a long time.

118
00:06:49,220 --> 00:06:50,659
I want to chat with you.

119
00:06:51,100 --> 00:06:52,380
Don’t turn us down.

120
00:06:53,659 --> 00:06:54,300
Okay.

121
00:06:54,860 --> 00:06:56,500
Sorry to bother you, then.

122
00:06:57,140 --> 00:06:59,740
We’ve been in BeipingPeking for a year.

123
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:03,820
Originally there were thirty-seven of us.

124
00:07:04,340 --> 00:07:07,100
Now only twenty-five of us are still here.

125
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:08,900
Some people

126
00:07:09,140 --> 00:07:10,300
got married.

127
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:12,540
Some broke the rules

128
00:07:12,860 --> 00:07:14,220
and were kicked out by me.

129
00:07:14,580 --> 00:07:15,780
Some despised

130
00:07:16,380 --> 00:07:18,300
our small troupe

131
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:21,060
and went to play walk-on roles for big troupes.

132
00:07:21,460 --> 00:07:22,260
Considering

133
00:07:22,260 --> 00:07:24,940
we’ve worked together for years,

134
00:07:25,460 --> 00:07:29,460
I’ve been turning a blind eye to your doings

135
00:07:30,020 --> 00:07:31,340
and I didn’t punish you.

136
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:35,020
Shijiu...

137
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:38,140
Shijiu had a good point.

138
00:07:38,580 --> 00:07:39,700
Shuiyun Theater

139
00:07:39,940 --> 00:07:41,140
is not the Shang Troupe.

140
00:07:41,420 --> 00:07:43,700
It’s not my own business.

141
00:07:44,420 --> 00:07:45,180
But

142
00:07:46,180 --> 00:07:48,460
if it has anyone’s service contract,

143
00:07:49,380 --> 00:07:51,900
he still belongs to Shuiyun Theater.

144
00:07:54,020 --> 00:07:55,940
Go and bring

145
00:07:56,700 --> 00:07:59,060
those who are outside back.

146
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:00,860
We’ll have a meeting

147
00:08:01,380 --> 00:08:02,580
at eight tonight

148
00:08:03,020 --> 00:08:03,900
and none shall be absent.

149
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:07,580
Whether Shuiyun Theater can survive

150
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:09,620
will depend on you.

151
00:08:09,820 --> 00:08:11,780
What if they really don’t want to come back?

152
00:08:13,620 --> 00:08:14,860
Just tell them

153
00:08:15,340 --> 00:08:16,620
as long as they arrive on time,

154
00:08:16,940 --> 00:08:18,380
I’ll return their contracts

155
00:08:18,580 --> 00:08:20,820
whatever the result is.

156
00:08:22,140 --> 00:08:23,580
Well...

157
00:08:26,780 --> 00:08:28,020
Stop looking at me.

158
00:08:28,020 --> 00:08:28,860
Go right now.

159
00:08:28,860 --> 00:08:30,300
It’s hard to travel when it’s dark.

160
00:08:30,380 --> 00:08:31,420
The men, go.

161
00:08:31,420 --> 00:08:32,580
Let’s go. Come on.

162
00:08:32,580 --> 00:08:33,659
Go, go, go.

163
00:08:40,419 --> 00:08:41,220
Slowly.

164
00:09:03,700 --> 00:09:06,340
After I left China with my parents at the age of eight,

165
00:09:06,780 --> 00:09:08,100
this is the first time I’ve been back.

166
00:09:09,460 --> 00:09:10,460
Over the past few years,

167
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:13,860
the world has changed dramatically.

168
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:17,060
But China is still the same.

169
00:09:18,540 --> 00:09:19,700
Changes of China

170
00:09:20,020 --> 00:09:22,100
aren’t things that can be seen.

171
00:09:23,300 --> 00:09:25,820
For example, the mansion in front of us

172
00:09:26,020 --> 00:09:28,820
looks the same as it was a hundred years ago

173
00:09:29,180 --> 00:09:30,820
because we’ve been maintaining it.

174
00:09:32,060 --> 00:09:34,140
But there are light bulbs and a phone inside

175
00:09:34,620 --> 00:09:36,900
and its residents also change from nobles of the former dynasty

176
00:09:37,260 --> 00:09:38,900
to modern gentlemen.

177
00:09:40,820 --> 00:09:42,260
Mr. Xin, you didn’t know.

178
00:09:42,780 --> 00:09:43,780
My brother-in-law is

179
00:09:43,860 --> 00:09:45,300
an astute businessman.

180
00:09:45,740 --> 00:09:46,580
But when he was

181
00:09:46,620 --> 00:09:47,860
going to buy this mansion

182
00:09:47,860 --> 00:09:49,380
to please my sister,

183
00:09:49,380 --> 00:09:50,420
he was fooled

184
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:51,700
and spent twice as much on it.

185
00:09:51,820 --> 00:09:53,500
Don’t you think he’s stupid?

186
00:09:54,900 --> 00:09:57,700
There are things that can’t be measured with money.

187
00:09:58,140 --> 00:09:58,980
Yes, yes, yes.

188
00:09:58,980 --> 00:10:00,700
Houses here are gorgeous.

189
00:10:01,700 --> 00:10:03,380
Perhaps it’s an occupational disease of me.

190
00:10:04,060 --> 00:10:06,340
Iif it were me, I would think they’re worth

191
00:10:06,540 --> 00:10:08,060
buying no matter how much they cost.

192
00:10:09,620 --> 00:10:11,060
Now that you like them,

193
00:10:11,580 --> 00:10:12,980
why don’t you let me show you around?

194
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:14,300
That will be great.

195
00:10:14,420 --> 00:10:15,060
Come on.

196
00:10:15,940 --> 00:10:16,460
Okay.

197
00:10:19,940 --> 00:10:22,820
Constructions of China are really beautiful.

198
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:27,220
You’ve maintained them well, Mr. Cheng.

199
00:10:28,540 --> 00:10:29,220
Thanks.

200
00:10:30,780 --> 00:10:31,780
As a Chinese,

201
00:10:31,780 --> 00:10:34,420
I’m obliged to preserve China’s history.

202
00:10:42,060 --> 00:10:42,660
Fengtai,

203
00:10:42,940 --> 00:10:43,700
Mr. Xin,

204
00:10:43,860 --> 00:10:44,660
you go on ahead.

205
00:10:44,660 --> 00:10:45,660
I’ll go to the kitchen and check.

206
00:10:46,820 --> 00:10:47,340
Okay.

207
00:10:49,020 --> 00:10:49,780
Be careful.

208
00:10:59,380 --> 00:11:00,980
You’ve really grown up.

209
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:03,340
You’re so quiet and pretty,

210
00:11:05,020 --> 00:11:06,580
just like a picture.

211
00:11:09,380 --> 00:11:10,540
Listen,

212
00:11:10,660 --> 00:11:12,380
we’ll have lunch with a guest later.

213
00:11:12,460 --> 00:11:13,780
You mustn’t pull a long face in front of your sister

214
00:11:13,820 --> 00:11:15,260
like you usually do.

215
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:23,420
I know you don’t like her.

216
00:11:24,220 --> 00:11:25,580
But you can’t humiliate us

217
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:28,020
when a guest is there.

218
00:11:28,820 --> 00:11:29,740
If people know about it,

219
00:11:29,740 --> 00:11:30,740
it’ll do you lots of harm

220
00:11:30,740 --> 00:11:32,220
and no men will dare to marry you.

221
00:11:36,140 --> 00:11:37,620
When did Mr. Cheng say we’ll have lunch?

222
00:11:37,820 --> 00:11:38,900
He just sent word

223
00:11:39,300 --> 00:11:40,780
that they were looking around the house.

224
00:11:41,260 --> 00:11:43,420
Everything can amaze that foreigner.

225
00:11:44,420 --> 00:11:45,500
Why didn’t you tell me earlier?

226
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:51,860
Let’s avoid him.

227
00:11:51,860 --> 00:11:52,900
Come on.

228
00:11:52,900 --> 00:11:53,900
It’s our house.

229
00:11:54,220 --> 00:11:55,580
Why should we avoid him?

230
00:11:56,860 --> 00:11:57,740
Hey,

231
00:11:58,100 --> 00:11:59,420
now you can answer back.

232
00:12:36,700 --> 00:12:37,500
Mr. Cheng,

233
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:40,420
can I have a look at the structure inside?

234
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:41,180
Sure.

235
00:12:41,900 --> 00:12:43,220
Fetch a tall ladder.

236
00:12:43,220 --> 00:12:44,220
Yes, Mr. Cheng.

237
00:12:53,620 --> 00:12:54,460
Be careful.

238
00:13:03,540 --> 00:13:05,260
What... what’s he doing?

239
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:08,740
I’ll tell you later.

240
00:13:17,260 --> 00:13:18,860
Oh, my God.

241
00:13:29,980 --> 00:13:32,260
How ingenious!.

242
00:13:33,460 --> 00:13:34,540
Awesome.

243
00:13:39,020 --> 00:13:40,540
How could I not think of this?

244
00:13:42,140 --> 00:13:44,940
This mansion is shockproof just because

245
00:13:45,700 --> 00:13:49,300
the roof is heavy enough.

246
00:13:50,180 --> 00:13:52,660
That’s also true of a cave.

247
00:13:54,260 --> 00:13:55,900
I don’t know what you mean.

248
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:00,500
What I mean is

249
00:14:01,940 --> 00:14:04,540
that Cave Liuxian can be saved now.

250
00:14:05,540 --> 00:14:08,180
But the one who can save it is not me

251
00:14:08,460 --> 00:14:09,900
but the builder of this house.

252
00:14:10,940 --> 00:14:13,100
As long as the structure is ingenious enough,

253
00:14:13,380 --> 00:14:15,660
the lack of bearing capacity of those materials

254
00:14:15,660 --> 00:14:17,660
will be solved smoothly.

255
00:14:18,860 --> 00:14:21,900
But this house was built a hundred years ago.

256
00:14:22,220 --> 00:14:24,460
The architect must have passed away.

257
00:14:25,220 --> 00:14:26,220
Professor Dr. Xin,

258
00:14:26,460 --> 00:14:27,660
can you copy it?

259
00:14:31,100 --> 00:14:36,100
Then I’ll have to at will need me to take the roof apart and see the whole structure

260
00:14:36,860 --> 00:14:39,820
and give me I need a few years to make a model of it.

261
00:14:40,140 --> 00:14:41,860
Can you wait so long?

262
00:14:44,180 --> 00:14:45,060
Mr. Xin,

263
00:14:45,740 --> 00:14:47,700
you don’t have to tear this house down

264
00:14:47,900 --> 00:14:49,700
to see its structure.

265
00:15:05,340 --> 00:15:07,540
I kept this when we bought

266
00:15:07,540 --> 00:15:08,700
this mansion.

267
00:15:11,980 --> 00:15:13,380
My wife is so careful.

268
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:18,780
Someone’s here.

269
00:15:34,980 --> 00:15:36,100
Genius.

270
00:15:36,940 --> 00:15:38,140
What a genius!.

271
00:15:39,540 --> 00:15:40,100
Look.

272
00:15:40,660 --> 00:15:42,300
The tenons and mortises here.

273
00:15:43,020 --> 00:15:44,140
This is unimaginable.

274
00:15:44,340 --> 00:15:45,740
Chinese people have known how to

275
00:15:45,740 --> 00:15:48,180
avoid buildings collapsing for centuries.

276
00:15:53,900 --> 00:15:55,500
But even if we have this drawing,

277
00:15:56,260 --> 00:15:58,140
we still can’t solve problems of Cave Liuxian.

278
00:15:59,220 --> 00:16:00,060
If you need years

279
00:16:00,060 --> 00:16:01,540
to study this,

280
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:04,140
that will be too long.

281
00:16:07,260 --> 00:16:10,020
There’s not just one person who can. Perhaps other people can also build this kind of house.

282
00:16:10,380 --> 00:16:12,860
You can look for someone who’s still alive.

283
00:16:14,180 --> 00:16:16,060
Do you know such a person?

284
00:16:16,820 --> 00:16:17,780
No.

285
00:16:18,140 --> 00:16:20,860
It’s just something I heard of.

286
00:16:22,020 --> 00:16:25,340
But I have an aunt who’s a princess of Mongolia.

287
00:16:25,780 --> 00:16:27,180
She said in the year of Gengzi,

288
00:16:27,580 --> 00:16:29,540
foreigners burned the Old Summer Palace.

289
00:16:30,380 --> 00:16:32,300
The Lei family tried to stopped them

290
00:16:32,300 --> 00:16:33,060
but failed.

291
00:16:33,660 --> 00:16:35,580
Some of them were burned to death.

292
00:16:37,300 --> 00:16:38,340
The Lei family?

293
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:39,980
I mean

294
00:16:40,020 --> 00:16:41,020
the Yangshi Leis

295
00:16:41,540 --> 00:16:43,660
who had been building houses in the palace for generations.

296
00:16:44,420 --> 00:16:46,660
Their craftsmanship has been there for over a hundred years.

297
00:16:47,660 --> 00:16:50,060
I guess this mansion

298
00:16:50,060 --> 00:16:51,660
is almost the same as those in the palace.

299
00:16:51,980 --> 00:16:54,780
Perhaps descendants of the Lei family can do it.

300
00:16:56,500 --> 00:16:58,100
It’s just hearsay.

301
00:16:58,100 --> 00:16:59,380
Just for your information.

302
00:17:00,340 --> 00:17:02,620
We’ll have lunch when you’re done.

303
00:17:07,619 --> 00:17:08,339
Mr. Cheng,

304
00:17:09,099 --> 00:17:11,780
I can’t guarantee that problems of Cave Liuxian can be solved

305
00:17:11,780 --> 00:17:13,859
after you find descendants of the Lei family.

306
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:16,500
But I’m sure

307
00:17:17,020 --> 00:17:19,099
if they can’t do it,

308
00:17:19,819 --> 00:17:20,980
no one will be capable of it.

309
00:17:28,540 --> 00:17:30,100
Yangshi Lei.

310
00:17:30,260 --> 00:17:32,540
Yangshi Lei is Yangshi Lei.

311
00:17:32,540 --> 00:17:34,380
Carving pillars and making eaves fly.

312
00:17:34,380 --> 00:17:36,260
Need no nails. Need no hammers.

313
00:17:36,260 --> 00:17:38,220
They just piled it up with wood.

314
00:17:39,980 --> 00:17:41,140
That’s so miraculous.

315
00:17:41,140 --> 00:17:42,180
Did you just make it up?

316
00:17:42,900 --> 00:17:43,740
Nonsense.

317
00:17:44,020 --> 00:17:45,580
How could I make that up?

318
00:17:45,780 --> 00:17:48,540
There’s really a Yangshi Lei here.

319
00:17:48,580 --> 00:17:50,820
He lives to the south of this street.

320
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:26,260
You say it.

321
00:18:26,260 --> 00:18:27,060
Say it. Say it.

322
00:18:27,060 --> 00:18:28,140
Quickly.

323
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:29,860
Quickly.

324
00:18:30,140 --> 00:18:31,580
- Say it. - Quickly.

325
00:18:37,220 --> 00:18:37,940
Leader,

326
00:18:39,300 --> 00:18:42,140
just please give our service contracts back to us.

327
00:18:42,260 --> 00:18:43,020
What’s the rush?

328
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:45,380
Some aren’t here yet.

329
00:18:45,380 --> 00:18:46,460
I’m not rushing you

330
00:18:46,580 --> 00:18:47,980
but I have things to do at home.

331
00:18:48,140 --> 00:18:48,740
Right.

332
00:18:48,740 --> 00:18:50,300
Me, too.

333
00:18:50,660 --> 00:18:51,180
Leader,

334
00:18:51,460 --> 00:18:52,500
just be frank with us.

335
00:18:52,700 --> 00:18:54,540
I need to go home and have dinner.

336
00:18:54,540 --> 00:18:56,060
Yes, me, too.

337
00:18:56,620 --> 00:18:57,540
Make it quick.

338
00:19:28,060 --> 00:19:29,220
It’s about time.

339
00:19:30,260 --> 00:19:31,300
Those who didn’t come here

340
00:19:33,020 --> 00:19:34,340
have made their choices.

341
00:19:36,900 --> 00:19:37,620
We’ll stop waiting for them.

342
00:19:38,780 --> 00:19:39,940
It’s hard to guard against inside theft.

343
00:19:41,020 --> 00:19:43,820
Our money was all taken away.

344
00:19:44,540 --> 00:19:45,740
It’s also hard to handle rumors.

345
00:19:46,540 --> 00:19:49,380
Theaters are afraid of offending Commander Cao

346
00:19:50,740 --> 00:19:52,860
and don’t want us to be on their stages.

347
00:19:55,100 --> 00:19:56,580
We’ve been so unlucky

348
00:19:57,860 --> 00:19:59,820
and I can’t go on like this

349
00:19:59,820 --> 00:20:01,500
with all of you.

350
00:20:01,660 --> 00:20:02,620
Leader, you’re not to blame.

351
00:20:02,620 --> 00:20:05,420
Before we came to BeipingPeking,

352
00:20:06,340 --> 00:20:08,140
you all gave it the nod.

353
00:20:09,660 --> 00:20:12,500
You hoped you could put on big plays

354
00:20:13,380 --> 00:20:14,500
and become rich

355
00:20:15,780 --> 00:20:16,860
in BeipingPeking.

356
00:20:18,260 --> 00:20:20,220
I failed your expectations

357
00:20:20,700 --> 00:20:21,500
and didn’t make them come true.

358
00:20:23,300 --> 00:20:24,180
Now

359
00:20:25,220 --> 00:20:26,700
we’re at a critical point.

360
00:20:28,540 --> 00:20:31,260
I’ve got to gather you

361
00:20:32,020 --> 00:20:33,020
to figure something out.

362
00:20:36,540 --> 00:20:38,060
You have to tell me

363
00:20:39,580 --> 00:20:42,260
whether Shuiyun Theater should still exist.

364
00:20:50,780 --> 00:20:51,500
Well...

365
00:20:51,860 --> 00:20:53,460
- What do we do? - Shall we leave or not?

366
00:20:55,580 --> 00:20:57,660
We’re a troupe. How can we just leave?

367
00:20:57,660 --> 00:20:58,740
That’s true.

368
00:21:14,380 --> 00:21:16,220
Some of you joined this troupe earlier than me

369
00:21:17,500 --> 00:21:19,020
and some later.

370
00:21:20,180 --> 00:21:22,540
Some of you grew up with me.

371
00:21:24,540 --> 00:21:26,060
How many years will it take

372
00:21:27,060 --> 00:21:27,940
to form a troupe?

373
00:21:29,220 --> 00:21:30,300
More than ten years.

374
00:21:32,420 --> 00:21:33,260
If you wanna break it,

375
00:21:35,820 --> 00:21:37,220
just say a word.

376
00:21:39,140 --> 00:21:40,620
What you did

377
00:21:41,260 --> 00:21:42,860
for Shuiyun Theater

378
00:21:43,740 --> 00:21:44,820
and suffered

379
00:21:46,620 --> 00:21:48,340
are much more than me.

380
00:21:50,780 --> 00:21:51,460
Well,

381
00:21:53,220 --> 00:21:54,380
I can sing

382
00:21:56,180 --> 00:21:57,380
but I have no wish

383
00:21:58,700 --> 00:21:59,980
for managing a troupe.

384
00:22:01,660 --> 00:22:02,940
And I’m not cunning enough.

385
00:22:05,860 --> 00:22:08,020
I’m most at fault

386
00:22:11,420 --> 00:22:12,860
that we’re splitting up today.

387
00:22:41,100 --> 00:22:42,740
These are your service contracts.

388
00:22:55,980 --> 00:22:56,900
Leader.

389
00:23:01,580 --> 00:23:02,620
He burned them.

390
00:23:10,500 --> 00:23:11,820
This is mine.

391
00:23:15,340 --> 00:23:16,420
I’ll keep it.

392
00:23:18,700 --> 00:23:20,140
As long as I’m alive,

393
00:23:21,700 --> 00:23:22,900
Shuiyun Theater will still exist.

394
00:23:23,580 --> 00:23:24,140
Leader,

395
00:23:24,460 --> 00:23:25,060
I’ll stay, too.

396
00:23:25,060 --> 00:23:25,980
I’m not leaving, either.

397
00:23:26,300 --> 00:23:27,340
What can we do?

398
00:23:27,660 --> 00:23:28,980
Join another troupe?

399
00:23:29,620 --> 00:23:30,500
Shuiyun Theater is the best.

400
00:23:30,500 --> 00:23:31,260
Right. Right.

401
00:23:31,340 --> 00:23:32,100
We can’t split up.

402
00:23:32,460 --> 00:23:33,380
I’m not leaving.

403
00:23:33,580 --> 00:23:35,180
I think I’m fine here.

404
00:23:35,340 --> 00:23:37,300
- At least I can eat well. - Yes.

405
00:23:37,580 --> 00:23:39,140
We don’t have friends in BeipingPeking.

406
00:23:39,460 --> 00:23:40,700
We should stay together.

407
00:23:41,260 --> 00:23:41,660
Yes.

408
00:23:41,700 --> 00:23:42,180
I’m not leaving.

409
00:23:42,180 --> 00:23:43,420
- Me, neither. - Me, neither.

410
00:23:43,420 --> 00:23:43,980
- We’re not leaving. - Me, neither.

411
00:23:43,980 --> 00:23:44,820
We’ll stay with you.

412
00:23:45,140 --> 00:23:46,260
Yes, we’ll stay with you.

413
00:23:46,380 --> 00:23:46,980
We’ll stay with you.

414
00:23:46,980 --> 00:23:47,860
We’ll all stay with you.

415
00:23:48,780 --> 00:23:49,780
- We’re not leaving. - Not leaving.

416
00:23:49,820 --> 00:23:50,420
No.Yes.

417
00:23:57,180 --> 00:23:57,940
Good!

418
00:24:01,740 --> 00:24:03,220
I burned all your contracts.

419
00:24:04,300 --> 00:24:05,060
Without bonds,

420
00:24:05,060 --> 00:24:06,700
I believe you’re all telling the truth.

421
00:24:08,340 --> 00:24:09,660
You didn’t fail Shuiyun Theater.

422
00:24:11,300 --> 00:24:12,820
I must live up to your expectations.

423
00:24:13,660 --> 00:24:14,660
We can’t stay in BeipingPeking any longer.

424
00:24:16,380 --> 00:24:17,740
There’s no reason

425
00:24:17,740 --> 00:24:19,140
for being so obstinate.

426
00:24:22,220 --> 00:24:23,100
We’ll go back to Pingyang!

427
00:24:26,780 --> 00:24:27,820
Excuse me.

428
00:24:44,460 --> 00:24:45,300
Leader,

429
00:24:45,700 --> 00:24:46,340
look.

430
00:24:46,340 --> 00:24:48,300
This hat has been missing for such a long time

431
00:24:48,300 --> 00:24:49,820
and now we found it.

432
00:24:52,620 --> 00:24:53,620
It’s just that

433
00:24:53,860 --> 00:24:55,300
it was broken

434
00:24:55,300 --> 00:24:56,460
by rats.

435
00:25:01,620 --> 00:25:02,380
Throw it away.

436
00:25:08,820 --> 00:25:10,900
How about these vases?

437
00:25:11,140 --> 00:25:12,300
They’re pretty new.

438
00:25:12,580 --> 00:25:14,220
They’ll break on the way.

439
00:25:15,100 --> 00:25:16,340
Give them to someone.

440
00:25:21,780 --> 00:25:22,820
And those

441
00:25:24,180 --> 00:25:25,660
gold and silver stuff.

442
00:25:26,020 --> 00:25:27,980
Sell those that can’t be used

443
00:25:28,300 --> 00:25:30,060
on stages.

444
00:25:30,620 --> 00:25:31,940
Sell those fans as well.

445
00:25:32,340 --> 00:25:33,700
We’ll need some money.

446
00:25:38,500 --> 00:25:42,380
How about these snuff bottles?

447
00:25:42,460 --> 00:25:43,340
Sell all of them.

448
00:25:44,460 --> 00:25:46,060
No one likes them in Pingyang.

449
00:25:49,180 --> 00:25:50,500
Keep the best two of them

450
00:25:51,300 --> 00:25:52,660
for Niu Baiwen.

451
00:25:53,460 --> 00:25:54,740
He has been supportive of us.

452
00:25:58,060 --> 00:25:58,740
Xiuzhi,

453
00:25:59,180 --> 00:26:00,180
take this away.

454
00:26:01,340 --> 00:26:01,940
Here you go.

455
00:26:02,140 --> 00:26:02,900
Be careful.

456
00:26:05,340 --> 00:26:05,900
Oh.

457
00:26:13,900 --> 00:26:14,420
Leader,

458
00:26:14,900 --> 00:26:16,420
how about these rings?

459
00:26:16,780 --> 00:26:18,940
Why don’t we keep the shiniest one?

460
00:26:19,420 --> 00:26:20,100
We can

461
00:26:20,620 --> 00:26:21,580
match it with costumes

462
00:26:21,940 --> 00:26:23,020
on stages.

463
00:26:24,380 --> 00:26:25,260
You decide.

464
00:26:30,660 --> 00:26:31,220
Wait.

465
00:26:42,940 --> 00:26:43,620
I won.

466
00:26:45,860 --> 00:26:47,380
Give me your money.

467
00:26:47,940 --> 00:26:48,780
I think

468
00:26:49,620 --> 00:26:50,820
I’m in luck now.

469
00:26:52,700 --> 00:26:53,180
Here,

470
00:26:53,460 --> 00:26:54,100
wear it.

471
00:26:58,660 --> 00:27:00,140
I’ve just known Cheng Fengtai

472
00:27:01,260 --> 00:27:02,900
for a few days

473
00:27:04,540 --> 00:27:06,100
and now I’m running away dejectedly.

474
00:27:07,940 --> 00:27:08,700
Leader,

475
00:27:09,500 --> 00:27:12,060
don’t get cross.

476
00:27:15,220 --> 00:27:17,780
Mr. Cheng is a wealthy man

477
00:27:18,220 --> 00:27:19,820
and he can pull us through

478
00:27:19,820 --> 00:27:22,060
with a little bit money.

479
00:27:23,140 --> 00:27:25,460
And we won’t accept it without repaying him.

480
00:27:25,780 --> 00:27:29,180
We can take our time to pay it back with interest.

481
00:27:29,780 --> 00:27:30,580
No.

482
00:27:31,740 --> 00:27:34,020
I can borrow from anyone except him.

483
00:27:34,460 --> 00:27:34,980
You...

484
00:27:37,540 --> 00:27:39,340
you are so stubborn.

485
00:27:41,180 --> 00:27:42,020
You don’t understandknow.

486
00:27:44,300 --> 00:27:47,020
Other people just like my plays.

487
00:27:47,860 --> 00:27:51,140
Cheng Fengtai understands me.

488
00:27:52,380 --> 00:27:54,220
Our friendship is different.

489
00:27:56,220 --> 00:27:58,260
I have to live up to his praises.

490
00:28:00,380 --> 00:28:01,180
Besides,

491
00:28:01,940 --> 00:28:04,260
he asked me to sing for his son

492
00:28:05,180 --> 00:28:06,420
and I messed it up.

493
00:28:07,580 --> 00:28:09,300
How can I take a mile?

494
00:28:12,700 --> 00:28:14,100
No wonder peopleyou can die

495
00:28:14,940 --> 00:28:16,460
for a bosom friend.

496
00:28:18,140 --> 00:28:19,340
When you have

497
00:28:20,380 --> 00:28:21,780
a bosom friend,

498
00:28:23,260 --> 00:28:25,300
you always feel you owe him something

499
00:28:26,380 --> 00:28:27,740
and you can’t repay it.

500
00:28:28,620 --> 00:28:30,340
Your friendship

501
00:28:30,900 --> 00:28:32,180
is too complex.

502
00:28:33,660 --> 00:28:34,700
I can’t get youit.

503
00:28:51,100 --> 00:28:53,020
Whose wife is this?

504
00:28:53,100 --> 00:28:54,260
Nothing is being blown or beaten.

505
00:28:54,340 --> 00:28:55,460
And she doesn’t bring any dowry.

506
00:28:55,500 --> 00:28:56,700
This is too quiet.

507
00:28:56,700 --> 00:28:58,900
She’s Mr. Xue’s new concubine.

508
00:28:58,900 --> 00:29:00,380
He married another woman.

509
00:29:00,380 --> 00:29:01,500
Who is it?

510
00:29:01,500 --> 00:29:03,340
It’s said that she’s a player.

511
00:29:03,420 --> 00:29:05,060
His mother thinks it’s disgraceful

512
00:29:05,060 --> 00:29:06,060
and don’t doesn’t allow him to spend too much.

513
00:29:06,660 --> 00:29:07,460
How many women

514
00:29:07,620 --> 00:29:08,940
has he married?

515
00:29:09,180 --> 00:29:10,220
She’s the fourth one already.

516
00:29:10,220 --> 00:29:11,260
My goodness.

517
00:29:12,820 --> 00:29:14,340
What are you wretches talking about?

518
00:29:15,140 --> 00:29:16,220
It’s none of your business.

519
00:29:16,220 --> 00:29:17,140
Who are you?

520
00:29:17,220 --> 00:29:18,620
I’ll beat you to death if you say one more word!

521
00:29:19,220 --> 00:29:19,780
Get lost.

522
00:29:22,180 --> 00:29:22,740
Ma’am,

523
00:29:23,060 --> 00:29:24,220
my brother is here.

524
00:29:24,220 --> 00:29:26,060
Let me talk with him for a while.

525
00:29:26,300 --> 00:29:27,100
Concubine Xue,

526
00:29:27,300 --> 00:29:28,260
make it short.

527
00:29:28,580 --> 00:29:30,980
Mr. Xue will be angry if we’re late.

528
00:29:31,900 --> 00:29:32,860
Thanks.

529
00:29:34,700 --> 00:29:35,420
Layue,

530
00:29:37,140 --> 00:29:37,740
come here.

531
00:29:43,500 --> 00:29:44,420
Liuyue.

532
00:29:46,060 --> 00:29:47,020
What are you doing here?

533
00:29:48,380 --> 00:29:49,100
Liuyue,

534
00:29:49,900 --> 00:29:50,820
we’re going

535
00:29:51,300 --> 00:29:52,460
back to Pingyang.

536
00:29:53,100 --> 00:29:55,460
You’ll be alone in BeipingPeking.

537
00:29:55,460 --> 00:29:56,500
You’re going back to Pingyang?

538
00:29:59,300 --> 00:30:00,780
How come?

539
00:30:04,900 --> 00:30:06,060
Do you have to leave?

540
00:30:08,620 --> 00:30:09,340
It’s okay.

541
00:30:11,420 --> 00:30:12,140
Layue,

542
00:30:13,300 --> 00:30:14,260
from now on,

543
00:30:15,100 --> 00:30:16,740
I won’t be staying with you.

544
00:30:17,940 --> 00:30:20,060
You must take care of yourself.

545
00:30:21,500 --> 00:30:24,420
You need to be young to sing.

546
00:30:25,740 --> 00:30:27,420
It’s not something you can do for long.

547
00:30:37,180 --> 00:30:37,860
Take them.

548
00:30:38,540 --> 00:30:39,420
No, Liuyue.

549
00:30:39,660 --> 00:30:40,060
You keep them.

550
00:30:40,060 --> 00:30:40,780
Take them.

551
00:30:48,740 --> 00:30:50,620
Mr. Xue is rich.

552
00:30:52,060 --> 00:30:54,020
I won’t be short of moneyanymore.

553
00:31:02,380 --> 00:31:03,980
It’s the best thing I can earned

554
00:31:03,980 --> 00:31:05,380
for myself.

555
00:31:06,740 --> 00:31:08,260
I’ll have to stop here.

556
00:31:12,420 --> 00:31:14,900
If you get a chance in the future,

557
00:31:15,420 --> 00:31:16,900
you must do better than me.

558
00:31:20,180 --> 00:31:20,980
Liuyue,

559
00:31:22,300 --> 00:31:23,340
if they make you suffer,

560
00:31:24,100 --> 00:31:25,020
send someone to tell me.

561
00:31:25,580 --> 00:31:26,540
I’ll come and take you away.

562
00:31:33,180 --> 00:31:34,060
Concubine Xue,

563
00:31:34,220 --> 00:31:35,380
it’s about time.

564
00:31:35,460 --> 00:31:36,620
We should go in now.

565
00:31:38,900 --> 00:31:39,820
Off you go.

566
00:33:07,940 --> 00:33:08,660
Layuehong.

567
00:33:10,220 --> 00:33:12,020
We’ve been packing for ages

568
00:33:12,380 --> 00:33:13,100
and you

569
00:33:13,420 --> 00:33:14,620
went out for a walk.

570
00:33:22,260 --> 00:33:23,940
Where did you get these golden bracelets?

571
00:33:25,580 --> 00:33:26,380
Give them back to me.

572
00:33:29,220 --> 00:33:30,620
I know even if you don’t tell me.

573
00:33:31,820 --> 00:33:33,340
They were given by Liuyuehong.

574
00:33:33,900 --> 00:33:36,940
Concubine Xue is really generous.

575
00:33:37,620 --> 00:33:40,500
This bracelet weighs 150 grams at least.

576
00:33:42,060 --> 00:33:42,900
Give them back!

577
00:33:45,180 --> 00:33:45,580
Stop.

578
00:33:45,580 --> 00:33:46,140
Give them back to me!

579
00:33:46,140 --> 00:33:47,020
Stop. Stop.

580
00:33:47,020 --> 00:33:48,260
Give them back to me!

581
00:33:48,260 --> 00:33:48,820
Hold onto him.

582
00:33:48,820 --> 00:33:49,500
I’m not giving them.

583
00:33:49,500 --> 00:33:50,140
Give them back to me!

584
00:33:50,140 --> 00:33:50,740
Nope.

585
00:33:50,740 --> 00:33:51,420
Alright, calm down.

586
00:33:52,380 --> 00:33:54,380
Look at you.

587
00:33:54,980 --> 00:33:56,180
If you miss Liuyuehong,

588
00:33:56,340 --> 00:33:57,580
go and live with her.

589
00:33:57,660 --> 00:33:59,580
What do you shamelessly stay here for?

590
00:33:59,580 --> 00:34:02,100
Give the bracelets back to me!

591
00:34:02,100 --> 00:34:03,100
- Layuehong. - No.

592
00:34:03,100 --> 00:34:03,780
Stop arguing.

593
00:34:04,100 --> 00:34:04,780
The leader is here.

594
00:34:04,940 --> 00:34:05,820
What are you doing?

595
00:34:16,500 --> 00:34:17,179
Give them to me.

596
00:34:28,060 --> 00:34:29,820
You know they were given by Liuyue.

597
00:34:30,620 --> 00:34:31,659
Whyat did you grab them from him for?

598
00:34:37,620 --> 00:34:38,380
Take care of them.

599
00:34:40,060 --> 00:34:40,659
Alright,

600
00:34:41,460 --> 00:34:42,260
keep packing.

601
00:34:44,659 --> 00:34:45,540
Hurry up.

602
00:35:02,220 --> 00:35:02,820
Fengtai,

603
00:35:03,500 --> 00:35:05,580
would the capable man, Yangshi Lei, live here?

604
00:35:07,340 --> 00:35:08,980
Did the German fool you?

605
00:35:10,540 --> 00:35:12,300
I wasn’t told by Professor Dr. Xin.

606
00:35:13,100 --> 00:35:14,100
It’s very coincidental.

607
00:35:14,900 --> 00:35:16,580
I came to this place with Mr. Shang before

608
00:35:16,620 --> 00:35:17,620
and met someone.

609
00:35:18,140 --> 00:35:19,340
He sang a ballad

610
00:35:20,500 --> 00:35:22,220
and it mentioned Yangshi Lei.

611
00:35:23,700 --> 00:35:24,660
That man said

612
00:35:24,700 --> 00:35:26,740
he lived nearby.

613
00:35:27,740 --> 00:35:28,500
Fengtai,

614
00:35:28,700 --> 00:35:30,460
you’re really something.

615
00:35:30,700 --> 00:35:32,620
How can you take words of a ballad seriously?

616
00:35:33,380 --> 00:35:35,620
They were made up to rhyme with each other, okay?

617
00:35:40,580 --> 00:35:41,700
What should we do, then?

618
00:35:42,980 --> 00:35:44,580
Let’s ask someone.

619
00:35:44,820 --> 00:35:45,340
Okay.

620
00:35:52,940 --> 00:35:54,020
Aren’t Don’t you feel cold?

621
00:35:54,020 --> 00:35:54,620
Yes.

622
00:35:55,460 --> 00:35:56,220
Don’t get sick.

623
00:35:57,060 --> 00:35:57,620
Take this.

624
00:35:57,620 --> 00:35:58,180
Thank you.

625
00:35:58,460 --> 00:35:59,420
Thank you.

626
00:36:00,020 --> 00:36:01,500
Catch him!

627
00:36:01,540 --> 00:36:02,740
- He’s here. - Catch him!

628
00:36:02,740 --> 00:36:04,180
Catch him. Catch him.

629
00:36:04,260 --> 00:36:05,220
- Catch him. - Mr. Cheng.

630
00:36:05,220 --> 00:36:05,820
You’re mistaken.

631
00:36:06,260 --> 00:36:07,380
You’re Mr. Cheng.

632
00:36:07,700 --> 00:36:09,180
Give me some money.

633
00:36:09,700 --> 00:36:10,060
Mr. Cheng.

634
00:36:10,060 --> 00:36:11,260
Catch him. Hold onto his legs.

635
00:36:11,300 --> 00:36:13,020
You’re mistaken.

636
00:36:13,180 --> 00:36:14,820
- I haven’t got any money on me. - What are you doing?

637
00:36:15,580 --> 00:36:16,300
I don’t have it.

638
00:36:16,300 --> 00:36:17,660
I don’t have any money on me.

639
00:36:17,820 --> 00:36:19,700
Aren’t you Mr. Shang’s friend?

640
00:36:19,700 --> 00:36:20,820
Yes, yes, yes.

641
00:36:20,820 --> 00:36:21,740
Let go of him.

642
00:36:21,740 --> 00:36:22,260
Come here.

643
00:36:22,260 --> 00:36:22,940
Come here.

644
00:36:22,940 --> 00:36:23,980
Come, come, come.

645
00:36:25,180 --> 00:36:27,980
I’m the former manager of Nanfu Troupe, Xian’er.

646
00:36:28,020 --> 00:36:29,060
Hello, Mr. Cheng

647
00:36:29,060 --> 00:36:29,820
and Mr. Fan.

648
00:36:30,460 --> 00:36:31,260
You know me?

649
00:36:31,980 --> 00:36:33,940
As long as I get some money,

650
00:36:34,340 --> 00:36:35,860
I’ll watch plays in theaters

651
00:36:36,060 --> 00:36:37,340
or go to brothels.

652
00:36:37,420 --> 00:36:37,980
Those

653
00:36:38,420 --> 00:36:39,780
are my hobbies.

654
00:36:39,900 --> 00:36:41,500
You must have met my brother-in-law in a brothel

655
00:36:41,500 --> 00:36:42,820
and me in a theater.

656
00:36:48,380 --> 00:36:50,220
Where does the Yangshi Lei

657
00:36:51,100 --> 00:36:51,980
in the ballad you sang live?

658
00:36:52,220 --> 00:36:53,020
Sir,

659
00:36:53,180 --> 00:36:55,340
could you take me there?

660
00:36:56,500 --> 00:36:57,500
Yangshi Lei.

661
00:36:57,700 --> 00:36:58,700
A ballad.

662
00:37:00,340 --> 00:37:02,820
Why can’t I think of it?

663
00:37:13,380 --> 00:37:14,420
Think again.

664
00:37:16,300 --> 00:37:17,500
A ballad.

665
00:37:18,260 --> 00:37:19,300
My brain.

666
00:37:19,580 --> 00:37:21,260
A ballad.

667
00:37:25,300 --> 00:37:28,140
You sang well that time.

668
00:37:29,580 --> 00:37:30,860
My brain. Well,

669
00:37:30,900 --> 00:37:32,260
I really can’t think of it.

670
00:37:32,300 --> 00:37:33,260
Well...

671
00:37:33,620 --> 00:37:34,780
Well...

672
00:37:35,420 --> 00:37:36,140
I said

673
00:37:36,340 --> 00:37:37,460
I would pay you.

674
00:37:38,540 --> 00:37:39,940
I really can’t think of it.

675
00:37:40,060 --> 00:37:40,780
You... you...

676
00:37:43,020 --> 00:37:43,900
That’s all I have.

677
00:37:44,820 --> 00:37:46,980
You must be kidding me.

678
00:37:47,300 --> 00:37:48,100
I know.

679
00:37:48,180 --> 00:37:49,740
The guy in the ballad.

680
00:37:50,180 --> 00:37:50,940
I know.

681
00:37:50,940 --> 00:37:51,820
We’re neighbors.

682
00:37:52,260 --> 00:37:52,860
Kids,

683
00:37:52,900 --> 00:37:54,100
thank Mr. Cheng.

684
00:37:54,140 --> 00:37:54,700
Quickly.

685
00:37:54,700 --> 00:37:55,500
- Thanks, Mr. Cheng. - Thanks, Mr. Cheng.

686
00:37:55,500 --> 00:37:56,860
You just earned your cotton clothes

687
00:37:56,860 --> 00:37:58,140
and living expenses for this winter.

688
00:37:58,140 --> 00:37:58,780
Don’t. Don’t.

689
00:37:59,260 --> 00:38:01,060
Stand up. Stand up.

690
00:38:03,580 --> 00:38:06,060
After the Empress Dowager watched our play

691
00:38:06,340 --> 00:38:07,620
and rewarded us,

692
00:38:08,700 --> 00:38:10,740
we also thanked her like this.

693
00:38:13,180 --> 00:38:13,700
Mr. Cheng,

694
00:38:14,140 --> 00:38:15,140
come with me.

695
00:38:15,620 --> 00:38:17,140
Kids, go and have fun yourselves.

696
00:38:17,780 --> 00:38:18,540
Go, go.

697
00:38:18,660 --> 00:38:19,220
Let’s go.

698
00:38:20,460 --> 00:38:21,020
This way.

699
00:38:21,820 --> 00:38:23,020
Give it to me.

700
00:38:23,460 --> 00:38:24,660
Let me play with it.

701
00:38:25,060 --> 00:38:26,420
(The Lei’s Residence)

702
00:38:26,420 --> 00:38:26,980
Here we are.
(The Lei’s Residence)

703
00:38:26,980 --> 00:38:32,980
(The Lei’s Residence)

704
00:38:32,980 --> 00:38:33,540
Here?
(The Lei’s Residence)

705
00:38:33,540 --> 00:38:36,460
(The Lei’s Residence)

706
00:38:36,460 --> 00:38:37,220
Who is it?
(The Lei’s Residence)

707
00:38:37,220 --> 00:38:38,020
(The Lei’s Residence)

708
00:38:38,020 --> 00:38:39,420
I’m your bro.
(The Lei’s Residence)

709
00:38:43,740 --> 00:38:45,540
It’s not the Spring Festival yet.

710
00:38:45,980 --> 00:38:47,980
Are you here to wish me a Happy New Year

711
00:38:47,980 --> 00:38:49,300
or borrow food from me?

712
00:38:49,940 --> 00:38:50,540
I’m here

713
00:38:50,980 --> 00:38:52,780
to introduce two gentlemen.

714
00:38:58,580 --> 00:39:00,140
How many times have I told you?

715
00:39:00,580 --> 00:39:02,180
I won’t see strangers.

716
00:39:03,940 --> 00:39:04,660
Wait a minute.

717
00:39:07,380 --> 00:39:08,020
Is this

718
00:39:09,140 --> 00:39:10,900
a work of your family?

719
00:39:14,940 --> 00:39:15,660
What’s wrong?

720
00:39:16,580 --> 00:39:17,460
What’s wrong?

721
00:39:17,660 --> 00:39:18,900
Something bad happened.

722
00:39:19,100 --> 00:39:20,060
The house is collapsing

723
00:39:20,220 --> 00:39:21,980
and tiles were are falling.

724
00:39:21,980 --> 00:39:23,660
They hit his head

725
00:39:23,700 --> 00:39:25,100
and he came to get even with you.

726
00:39:25,100 --> 00:39:26,340
Impossible.

727
00:39:27,340 --> 00:39:30,260
Houses we build will stand for over five hundred years.

728
00:39:30,300 --> 00:39:31,460
Well...

729
00:39:38,220 --> 00:39:39,180
Come in.

730
00:39:39,500 --> 00:39:40,060
Okay.

731
00:39:40,140 --> 00:39:40,860
I have things to do.

732
00:39:41,100 --> 00:39:42,300
I’ll let you in yourselves.leave you alone.

733
00:39:42,420 --> 00:39:43,540
Go on. Go on. Go on.

734
00:39:43,540 --> 00:39:45,220
Thanks. Thanks. Thanks.

735
00:39:45,220 --> 00:39:50,380
♫ Stand in the main street ♫

736
00:39:50,380 --> 00:39:54,860
♫ And greet guests and friends that pass by ♫

737
00:40:10,140 --> 00:40:10,900
Hands off.

738
00:40:14,100 --> 00:40:15,180
You know this, too?

739
00:40:16,100 --> 00:40:16,660
No.

740
00:40:17,260 --> 00:40:18,940
When I was in college abroad,

741
00:40:19,420 --> 00:40:20,620
I studied architecture a bit

742
00:40:21,460 --> 00:40:22,700
and made a few models.

743
00:40:23,460 --> 00:40:24,780
But compared with yours,

744
00:40:24,780 --> 00:40:26,100
they’re really nothing.

745
00:40:26,380 --> 00:40:27,100
Originally

746
00:40:27,540 --> 00:40:29,740
it was prepared for the eightieth birthday of the Empress Dowager.

747
00:40:31,180 --> 00:40:34,140
My grandpa worked on it for two and a half years

748
00:40:34,780 --> 00:40:36,340
until one of his eyes was blinded.

749
00:40:36,940 --> 00:40:38,180
But unexpectedly, she passed away

750
00:40:38,740 --> 00:40:40,020
when he just finished this model.

751
00:40:43,460 --> 00:40:45,620
Your house used to be the mansion of a prince, right?

752
00:40:47,660 --> 00:40:48,900
I hear it belonged to Prince Shun.

753
00:40:49,500 --> 00:40:50,860
Their descendants were lousy

754
00:40:51,260 --> 00:40:53,980
and sold the mansion to me with the garden.

755
00:40:55,460 --> 00:40:57,460
Swallows which skimmed by painted eaves in bygone days

756
00:40:57,940 --> 00:41:00,220
Are dipping now among the humble homes’ doorways.

757
00:41:01,860 --> 00:41:02,940
Actually we’re not here

758
00:41:03,420 --> 00:41:04,980
for my house.

759
00:41:05,500 --> 00:41:08,140
It’s because I ran into difficulties with a project

760
00:41:08,540 --> 00:41:11,580
and I want to consult you.

761
00:41:13,980 --> 00:41:15,740
You flatter me.

762
00:41:17,180 --> 00:41:17,980
This way, please.

763
00:41:36,500 --> 00:41:37,260
Goodness.

764
00:41:38,500 --> 00:41:39,260
Fengtai,

765
00:41:39,700 --> 00:41:40,820
we’re in the right place.

766
00:41:41,540 --> 00:41:42,860
He’s really a Yangshi Lei.

767
00:41:43,980 --> 00:41:45,340
Look at these tenons and mortises.

768
00:41:48,700 --> 00:41:50,220
Even a hair can’t go through it.

769
00:42:01,100 --> 00:42:01,700
Mr. Lei,

770
00:42:01,900 --> 00:42:03,180
let me give you a piece of advice.

771
00:42:03,540 --> 00:42:06,100
You should give lectures in Europe.

772
00:42:06,420 --> 00:42:07,860
I believe countless universities will want you

773
00:42:08,020 --> 00:42:10,660
to be an honorary professor.

774
00:42:12,500 --> 00:42:14,340
You need to comprehend to do this kind of work.

775
00:42:14,940 --> 00:42:17,100
How can I teach others if I can’t describe it?

776
00:42:18,220 --> 00:42:19,420
You can write a book

777
00:42:20,020 --> 00:42:21,580
about this craftsmanship.

778
00:42:23,100 --> 00:42:24,900
I can only read pictures drawings and write numbers.

779
00:42:25,260 --> 00:42:28,620
I’m not quite literate.

780
00:42:29,740 --> 00:42:30,820
That’s hard to believe.

781
00:42:33,780 --> 00:42:35,580
Show me your

782
00:42:36,060 --> 00:42:37,260
engineering drawing.

783
00:42:41,660 --> 00:42:42,940
If you don’t trust me,

784
00:42:43,660 --> 00:42:46,180
please leave my house now.

785
00:42:51,980 --> 00:42:53,180
You brought me here

786
00:42:53,180 --> 00:42:54,260
and now you’re sending me away?

787
00:42:56,540 --> 00:42:58,020
I can’t believe this.
